{"type":"message","id":"f8ebf986","parentId":"41f32c1b","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:27:26.953Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_o7z9IeJG95VT6TmkOsE3H7ZX|fc_003023182b9e57460169c32bee6e3c81918913650dfe9b289e","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace\\MEMORY.md."}],"details":{"diff":"    ...\n  8 - Rol de Ares: ayudar a decidir el entrenamiento del día según energía y carga semanal; coordinar el grupo `Smart Project`.\n  9 - Personalidad deseada de Ares: directo, motivador, claro y práctico; sin motivación falsa ni teoría en exceso.\n 10 - Rutina base de Ares: torso-pierna frecuencia 2 — miércoles, jueves, sábado y domingo.\n 11 - Restricción crítica de Ares: solo escribir en `Smart Project` cuando Gustavo hable, hasta nueva orden de Gustavo.\n+12 - Preferencia operativa para grupos de WhatsApp compartidos: evitar que Atlas y el agente dueño del grupo (por ejemplo Ares en `Smart Project`) escriban o coordinen sobre el mismo chat al mismo tiempo; si Atlas necesita empujar algo, primero debe dejar liberar el canal y luego disparar solo al agente responsable para evitar colisiones de entrega/enrutado.\n 12 - Agente técnico ya creado: **Prometeo** (`🔥`), enfocado en TradeLab.\n 13 - Rol de Prometeo: priorizar, organizar y ejecutar lo que desbloquea el lanzamiento de TradeLab.\n 14 - Repositorio local principal de TradeLab para Prometeo: `C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\Documents\\tradelab-front`.\n 15 - Flujo de trabajo de Prometeo: trabajar sobre la rama `agent-workspace` y abrir pull requests hacia `main`.\n    ...","firstChangedLine":12},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774398446951}}
{"type":"message","id":"c621f79b","parentId":"f8ebf986","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:27:32.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_VefOhPUSgBRdwAOl7JW6ZfFh|fc_003023182b9e57460169c32bf461008191b7f7dac50d3786a4","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace\\AGENTS.md","old_string":"**Safe to do freely:**\n\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n","new_string":"**Safe to do freely:**\n\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\n- Search the web, check calendars\n- Work within this workspace\n\n## Shared-channel coordination\n\nWhen multiple agents share the same external channel/account (especially WhatsApp), avoid overlapping sends on the same chat. If Atlas is coordinating an agent-owned group, do not keep talking into that same chat while the owner agent is expected to reply. Let the channel settle, then trigger only the responsible agent and verify afterward. Prefer serialized handoffs over simultaneous writes.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\AGENTS.md\",\"old_string\":\"**Safe to do freely:**\\n\\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\\n- Search the web, check calendars\\n- Work within this workspace\\n\",\"new_string\":\"**Safe to do freely:**\\n\\n- Read files, explore, organize, learn\\n- Search the web, check calendars\\n- Work within this workspace\\n\\n## Shared-channel coordination\\n\\nWhen multiple agents share the same external channel/account (especially WhatsApp), avoid overlapping sends on the same chat. If Atlas is coordinating an agent-owned group, do not keep talking into that same chat while the owner agent is expected to reply. Let the channel settle, then trigger only the responsible agent and verify afterward. Prefer serialized handoffs over simultaneous writes.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":112,"output":187,"cacheRead":28544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28843,"cost":{"input":0.00028000000000000003,"output":0.002805,"cacheRead":0.007136,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.010221000000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774398446953,"responseId":"resp_003023182b9e57460169c32bf2cb2c8191bc306ccb4e56d4aa"}}
{"type":"message","id":"58e32135","parentId":"c621f79b","timestamp":"2026-03-25T00:27:32.886Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_VefOhPUSgBRdwAOl7JW6ZfFh|fc_003023182b9e57460169c32bf461008191b7f7dac50d3786a4","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace\\AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  59 - Read files, explore, organize, learn\n  60 - Search the web, check calendars\n  61 - Work within this workspace\n  62 \n+ 63 ## Shared-channel coordination\n+ 64 \n+ 65 When multiple agents share the same external channel/account (especially WhatsApp), avoid overlapping sends on the same chat. If Atlas is coordinating an agent-owned group, do not keep talking into that same chat while the owner agent is expected to reply. Let the channel settle, then trigger only the responsible agent and verify afterward. Prefer serialized handoffs over simultaneous writes.\n+ 66 \n  63 **Ask first:**\n  64 \n  65 - Sending emails, tweets, public posts\n  66 - Anything that leaves the machine\n     ...","firstChangedLine":63},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774398452884}}
